1451
02:10:18,429 --> 02:10:23,409
The Attack on Kemp's House

1452
02:10:23,409 --> 02:10:30,590
Kemp was reading a strange letter, written
in pencil on a dirty sheet of paper.

1453
02:10:30,590 --> 02:10:38,059
You have been very clever, though what you
gain by it I cannot think. You are against

1454
02:10:38,059 --> 02:10:46,290
me. For a whole day you have hunted me - you
have tried to rob me of a night's rest. But

1455
02:10:46,290 --> 02:10:55,800
I have had food, I have slept, and we are
only beginning. We are only beginning. There

1456
02:10:55,800 --> 02:11:04,280
is nothing to be done but to start the Terror.
This is the first day of the Terror. Port

1457
02:11:04,280 --> 02:11:12,040
Burdock is no longer under the Queen. Tell
your police, and the rest of them; it is under

1458
02:11:12,040 --> 02:11:23,170
me - the Terror! I am Invisible Man the First.
We shall begin with the death of a man named

1459
02:11:23,170 --> 02:11:32,540
Kemp. He will die today. He may hide himself
away, and collect guards around him; Death,

1460
02:11:32,540 --> 02:11:41,949
the unseen Death, is coming. The game begins.
Death starts. If you help him, my people,

1461
02:11:41,949 --> 02:11:51,559
Death may fall on you too. Today Kemp is to
die.

1462
02:11:51,559 --> 02:11:59,900
Kemp read this letter twice. 'That's his voice!'
