gunshot, and the broken glass fell into the

1497
02:15:11,960 --> 02:15:12,960
room.

1498
02:15:12,960 --> 02:15:15,900
'What's this for?' said Adye.

1499
02:15:15,900 --> 02:15:18,349
'It's beginning,' said Kemp.

1500
02:15:18,349 --> 02:15:21,000
'There's no way of climbing up here?'

1501
02:15:21,000 --> 02:15:24,679
'Not even for a cat,' said Kemp.

1502
02:15:24,679 --> 02:15:30,710
Stones came flying in and then it sounded
as if someone was banging on the windows downstairs.

1503
02:15:30,710 --> 02:15:34,300
The two men stood outside the study, not knowing
what to do.

1504
02:15:34,300 --> 02:15:39,889
'I know!' said Adye. 'Let me have a stick
or something, and I'll go down to the station

1505
02:15:39,889 --> 02:15:43,500
and get the man with the bloodhounds. They'll
find him.'

1506
02:15:43,500 --> 02:15:46,119
Another window broke.

1507
02:15:46,119 --> 02:15:49,280
'You haven't got a revolver?' asked Adye.

1508
02:15:49,280 --> 02:15:55,770
Kemp's hand went to his pocket. Then he paused.
'I haven't one - at least, none that I want

1509
02:15:55,770 --> 02:15:57,130
