1510
02:15:57,130 --> 02:16:01,929
'I'll bring it back,' said Adye. 'You'll be
safe here.'

1511
02:16:01,929 --> 02:16:05,079
Kemp gave him the weapon.

1512
02:16:05,079 --> 02:16:08,020
'Now for the door,' said Adye.

1513
02:16:08,020 --> 02:16:13,309
As they stood waiting in the hall, they heard
one of the bedroom windows crack. Kemp went

1514
02:16:13,309 --> 02:16:19,099
to the door and began to turn the key as silently
as he could. His face was a little paler than

1515
02:16:19,099 --> 02:16:20,099
usual.

1516
02:16:20,099 --> 02:16:23,780
'You must step straight out,' he said.

1517
02:16:23,780 --> 02:16:29,680
In another moment Adye was on the doorstep
and the door was shut. He waited for a moment,

1518
02:16:29,680 --> 02:16:35,050
feeling more comfortable with his back against
the door. Then he marched down the steps.

1519
02:16:35,050 --> 02:16:40,019
He crossed the grass and had almost reached
the gate when something moved near him.

1520
02:16:40,019 --> 02:16:46,300
'Stop a bit,' said a Voice, and Adye stopped,
with his hand on the revolver.

1521
02:16:46,300 --> 02:16:48,140
'Well?' said Adye.

1522
02:16:48,140 --> 02:16:52,890
'Please go back to the house,' said the Voice.

1523
02:16:52,890 --> 02:16:57,530
'No,' said Adye. He thought of trying a shot
in the direction of the Voice.

1524
02:16:57,530 --> 02:17:00,840
'What are you going to do?' said the Voice.

1525
02:17:00,840 --> 02:17:05,330
'What I do is my own business,' said Adye.

1526
02:17:05,330 --> 02:17:10,389
The words were still on his lips when an arm
came round his neck, he felt a knee in his

1527
02:17:10,389 --> 02:17:16,200
back, and his head was forced backward. He
fired the gun wildly, and in another moment

1528
02:17:16,200 --> 02:17:21,570
he was struck in the mouth and the weapon
was taken from his hand. He tried to struggle,

1529
02:17:21,570 --> 02:17:23,290
and was thrown on his back.

1530
02:17:23,290 --> 02:17:26,110
'You devil!' said Adye.

1531
02:17:26,110 --> 02:17:33,690
The Voice laughed. 'I would kill you now if
it wasn't a waste of a shot,' it said. Adye

1532
02:17:33,690 --> 02:17:38,149
saw the revolver in the air, 6 feet off, pointing
at him.

1533
02:17:38,149 --> 02:17:40,630
'Well?' said Adye, sitting up.

1534
02:17:40,630 --> 02:17:43,120
'Get up,' said the Voice.

1535
02:17:43,120 --> 02:17:44,969
Adye stood up.

1536
02:17:44,969 --> 02:17:52,331
'Stand still,' said the Voice, and then firmly.
'Don't try any tricks. Remember I can see

1537
02:17:52,331 --> 02:17:57,800
your face, if you can't see mine. You've got
to go back to the house.'

1538
02:17:57,800 --> 02:18:00,679
'He won't let me in,' said Adye.

1539
02:18:00,679 --> 02:18:06,179
'That's a pity,' said the Invisible Man. 'It
isn't you I want to kill.'

1540
02:18:06,179 --> 02:18:12,429
Adye glanced away from the revolver and saw
the sea far off, very blue and dark under

1541
02:18:12,429 --> 02:18:19,010
the bright sun. He saw the smooth green hill,
the white rocks of the coast, and the spreading

1542
02:18:19,010 --> 02:18:26,250
town, and suddenly he knew that life was very
sweet. His eyes came back to this little metal

1543
02:18:26,250 --> 02:18:34,960
thing hanging between heaven and earth, six
feet away. 'What must I do?' he asked.

1544
02:18:34,960 --> 02:18:43,410
'What must I do?' asked the Invisible Man.
'If I let you go, you'll get help. The only

1545
02:18:43,410 --> 02:18:46,899
thing is for you to go back to the house.'

1546
02:18:46,899 --> 02:18:54,269
'I'll try. If he lets me in, will you promise
not to charge the door?'

1547
02:18:54,269 --> 02:18:59,530
'I don't want to fight you,' said the Voice.

1548
02:18:59,530 --> 02:19:05,099
Kemp had hurried upstairs after letting Adye
out, and now, looking through a broken window,

1549
02:19:05,099 --> 02:19:12,679
he saw Adye stand talking with the unseen
enemy. 'Why doesn't he fire?' said Kemp to

1550
02:19:12,679 --> 02:19:15,340
himself. Then the revolver moved a little.

1551
02:19:15,340 --> 02:19:20,719
'That's strange!' he said. 'Adye has given
up the revolver.'

1552
02:19:20,719 --> 02:19:27,349
'Promise not to charge the door,' Adye was
saying. 'Give me a chance.'

1553
02:19:27,349 --> 02:19:32,760
'Just go back to the house. I tell you I'll
promise nothing.'

1554
02:19:32,760 --> 02:19:38,729
Adye seemed to decide suddenly. He turned
towards the house, and walked slowly with

1555
02:19:38,729 --> 02:19:46,219
his hands behind him. Kemp watched him. The
revolver appeared, a small dark object, following

1556
02:19:46,219 --> 02:19:53,631
Adye. Then things happened very quickly. Adye
jumped at the small object, missed it, threw

1557
02:19:53,631 --> 02:19:59,260
